---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import OutcomesComparison from '../components/OutcomesComparison.tsx';
---

<Layout title="Outcomes" description="The Now City Neighborhood benchmark vs. a traditional equivalent across six v1 metrics: ROI, timeline, cost of capital, carbon, economic development, and resilience.">
  <section class="pt-20 pb-12 md:pt-28">
    <div class="container-wide">
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <div class="eyebrow mb-6">Outcomes</div>
        <h1 class="text-display-xl font-display text-forest-700">
          Better projects. Better capital. Better outcomes.
        </h1>
        <p class="lede mt-8 text-stone-700">
          Regenerative development isn't a claim — it's a measurable
          difference across the dimensions that actually matter to
          landowners, operators, cities, and capital.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="pb-20">
    <div class="container-wide">
      <OutcomesComparison client:load />
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Methodology + honesty note -->
  <section class="border-t border-forest-700/10 bg-cream-50 py-20">
    <div class="container-wide grid gap-12 md:grid-cols-12">
      <div class="md:col-span-5">
        <div class="eyebrow mb-4">On the numbers</div>
        <h2 class="text-display-md font-display text-forest-700">
          We'd rather be precise than impressive.
        </h2>
      </div>
      <div class="md:col-span-7">
        <p class="prose-body">
          The ranges above are v1 directional claims, grounded in
          comparable-project benchmarks and internal modeling of the Now
          City Stack. They are honest approximations — not marketing
          inflation.
        </p>
        <p class="prose-body mt-5">
          As we close and operate additional projects, every metric will
          be anchored to primary-source data: NCREIF benchmarks for
          financial performance, full LCA reports for carbon, third-party
          audits for resilience tiering, and BLS/local-multiplier analysis
          for economic-development claims.
        </p>
        <p class="prose-body mt-5">
          If you're evaluating a specific site, we'll run this comparison
          against your actual land, capital stack, and program — not the
          benchmark. That's the gateway call.
        </p>
        <div class="mt-8">
          <a href="/services/#contact" class="btn-primary">Schedule a gateway call</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
